    <p class=maintext>
                <p>The secure online booking form is accessed as a popup window that can only be activated by the customer clicking on the 'Accept' button. Coupled with a suitable message, this implies that by placing an online booking on the site the customer agrees to the terms and conditions that are shown on the page. </p>
<p>A statement can also be shown that indicates that any online booking will remain unconfirmed until an email is sent confirming availability and indicating the owner's acceptance of the booking. This caveat gives the owner the right to accept or reject online bookings at their own discretion.</p>  
<p>To enable the EseBooking secure booking service on your site, all that is needed is to add the 'Accept' button to a page showing the relevant Terms and Conditions and any caveats as required.
<p>The secure booking form itself is designed for ease of use and simplicity. It only has the minimum number of fields required to capture the booking details, and it provides informative responses if the customer makes any errors in filling out the form. Prices are calculated using the rates set up in the EseBooking database, but they can be overridden in the Administration Console, giving you the flexibility to agree special rates with special customers. </p>
<p>Try it out for yourself! Click on the button below and fill in the form however you wish. You can check availability and resubmit the form as many times as you like! Remember, if you register for a username and password, you can access the Administration Console and work with any "test" bookings you make.</p>
<p><input type="button" name="conditions" value="Accept " onClick="DoPopup('dlockwood/esekey');"></p></p>
